The paper deals with community detection in random graphs, which is a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a modified adjacency matrix and the analysis of its spectral properties suggest that the paper may also fall under the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) categories. Finally, the study of community detection thresholds and the stochastic block model may also make the paper relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) category.
